===============================================================================
INSTALL - Installation Instructions for merge_conflict_detector
===============================================================================

DESCRIPTION
-----------
This document provides step-by-step installation instructions for the
merge_conflict_detector tool on POSIX-compliant systems.

REQUIREMENTS
------------
System Requirements:
  * POSIX-compliant operating system (Linux, Unix, macOS, BSD variants)
  * POSIX shell (/bin/sh)
  * POSIX C compiler (c99 compliant)
  * POSIX make utility
  * POSIX AWK implementation
  * Git version control system (>= 2.0)

POSIX Utilities Required:
  awk, basename, cat, chmod, cp, cut, date, diff, dirname,
  echo, expr, find, grep, head, mkdir, mv, printf, rm,
  sed, sh, sort, tail, test, touch, tr, wc, xargs

INSTALLATION METHODS
--------------------
Method 1: From Source (Recommended)
  1. Extract the source archive:
         tar -xzf merge_conflict_detector-1.0.tar.gz
         cd merge_conflict_detector-1.0
  2. Configure the build:
         make configure
  3. Compile the software:
         make
  4. Run tests (optional but recommended):
         make test
  5. Install to system:
         make install
  6. Install manual pages:
         make install-man

Method 2: User Installation (no root required)
         make PREFIX=$HOME/.local install
         export PATH=$HOME/.local/bin:$PATH

Method 3: Custom Installation Path
         make PREFIX=/opt/merge_detector install

BUILD CONFIGURATION
-------------------
Standard Configuration:
         make configure

Custom Compiler:
         make CC=gcc configure
         make

Custom Installation Paths:
  PREFIX   Installation prefix (default: /usr/local)
  BINDIR   Binary directory (default: $PREFIX/bin)
  MANDIR   Manual page directory (default: $PREFIX/share/man)
  LIBDIR   Library directory (default: $PREFIX/lib)

Example:
         make PREFIX=/usr BINDIR=/usr/bin MANDIR=/usr/share/man install

VERIFICATION
------------
Test Installation:
         merge_conflict_detector --help

Check Version:
         merge_conflict_detector --version

Run System Test:
         merge_conflict_detector --test-system

UNINSTALLATION
--------------
To remove the installed software:
         make uninstall

For custom installation paths:
         make PREFIX=/custom/path uninstall

TROUBLESHOOTING
---------------
"Command not found":
         export PATH=/usr/local/bin:$PATH

"Permission denied during installation":
         sudo make install
    Or install to user directory:
         make PREFIX=$HOME/.local install

"Compiler not found":
    # On Debian/Ubuntu
         apt-get install build-essential
    # On RHEL/CentOS
         yum groupinstall "Development Tools"
    # On Alpine Linux
         apk add build-base

"Make not found":
    # On Debian/Ubuntu
         apt-get install make
    # On RHEL/CentOS
         yum install make
    # On Alpine Linux
         apk add make

Build Errors:
  1. Check POSIX compliance of your system
  2. Verify all required utilities are installed
  3. Try using a different C compiler:
         make clean
         make CC=clang

Git Not Found:
    # On Debian/Ubuntu
         apt-get install git
    # On RHEL/CentOS
         yum install git
    # On Alpine Linux
         apk add git

PLATFORM-SPECIFIC NOTES
-----------------------
Linux:      Most distributions should work out of the box.
macOS:      Install Xcode command line tools: xcode-select --install
FreeBSD:    pkg install git gmake; make MAKE=gmake
Solaris:    make CC=/opt/SUNWspro/bin/cc

DEVELOPMENT INSTALLATION
------------------------
For development and contributing:
         git clone https://github.com/2MuchC0ff33/merge-conflict-detector.git
         cd merge_conflict_detector
         make configure
         make debug
         make test

FILES
-----
  Makefile         Main build configuration
  configure.sh     POSIX configuration script
  src/             Source code directory
  tests/           Test suite directory
  man/             Manual pages

SEE ALSO
--------
  make(1), git(1), README.txt, USAGE.txt, CONTRIBUTING.txt, https://github.com/2MuchC0ff33/merge-conflict-detector
===============================================================================
